				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Another pulling hard LDoN post...<a name="55737"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 9 04 12:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I have pulled 5 hard LDoN so far.
<br />
I have 280 CHA, JF 2, SM 1, Epic and VoTS.
<br />
2 BB the easy cavern types-went well.
<br />
1 easy spaced out ef
<br />
and 2 TAKs which where disasters altho we did finsh one in the last minute of timer <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
I have read all the excelent posts and guides here and just wanted to know you guys stragety in certain scenarios.
<br />

<br />
Scenario #1
<br />
I have problems with rooms that have 6+ mobs in them deciding which to pull to hoepfully have a split room on next try.
<br />
1.  Those hard TAK rooms with 6+ mobs in them what is your normal stragety? 
<br />

<br />
ex1. Would you mez the one closest to door, have a mob in the middle of room in target buffer, fade, and hope to kill the one in the middle of aggrso chain with rest of straglers after fade. 
<br />
or...
<br />

<br />
ex2. Try and lull a few closest to door and pray it works and pull another one or 2 close to door. Reason for this is has anyone noticed if you get a critical resist on mobs that they only aggreso those close to them or would whole room aggeso after each other?  Last night in a 3 mob room I had a critical resist on lulling a side mob and only the middle came with it, the oppiste mob that was just the same distance did not come.
<br />

<br />
2nd scenairo
<br />
I have been having problems with how exactly FM works.
<br />
Lets say I have a bad pull of 4+ mobs, then I  mez one and use FM immediatly.  Here is what happend the few times I did this.  Either the mobs reaggrsoed from my mezzed mob, or the mez wore off while they were in aggreso range and came and they reaggrosed me, or if you fade while you have a mezzed mob as soon as the mez wares off your still on it's aggreso list so you should fade after the mez wares off.  It was all so fast I couldn't tell exactly what happened.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for what advice you can give.</span></td>
