			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Another pulling hard LDoN posts...<a name="55742"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 9 04 12:21 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Tak dungeons aren't so bad now that I've had a lot more practice with them. The rooms you mention and especially the narrow hallways are daunting at first.
<br />

<br />
My usual way of handling high mob counts in pulls is to use mezz and lull. With dark blue mobs, lulling them at 280 charisma rarely brings critical resists for me and most of the time they dont resist at all(have had mobs resist non-critically 3 times in a row before it succeeds, white cons will almost always crit resist). If the room has 6+ mobs, mezzing the one in the front will generally split the pull to 4 or less.
<br />

<br />
The trick to breaking a pull of 4 or 5 mobs is to use kiting rooms. I generally keep my group back a good 3 or 4 rooms(sometimes they stay at the zone in the whole adventure).
<br />

<br />
Then, I break the pulls down as much as I can and if I grab 3 or more I will run them around a large room to get as many mezzed as I can before leading one to the group, then, I go back and make sure the ones I mezzed will filter through safely.
<br />

<br />
I have also noticed the mezz/fade bug each time I've faded after mezzing. I once mezzed a mob 2 rooms away, went to the group and faded(with mezz song stopped so it wont retick), and the mob still reaggroed after mezz broke. I don't rely on the fading off mezzed mobs anymore, instead I rely on keeping as many mezzed as I can or kite them around long enough to split them off to the group.
<br />

<br />
Lull darkblues and only darkblues and only if NOT lulling that darkblue would bring the same amount of mobs as if your lull crit failed. If your lull fails at least you don't bring more than what you started with. Utilize the large rooms to your advantage if a pull goes bad, kite them and have tank strip them off with an arrow or mezz them and lead one to the group.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

