				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Another pulling hard LDoN posts...<a name="55758"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 9 04 1:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>first, get planar power until charisma is at 305, substantially fewer crit fails with 305 than 280, believe me, it makes a huge difference.
<br />

<br />
Next, always have 2 targets in your target buffer... 2 unlulled ones that might add on a crit.  this way you can get 2 mezzed while you run (or one if only need to)
<br />

<br />
Lulling blues is easier of course, but whites are possible a lot with 305 charisma.
<br />

<br />
using one or more rooms/hallways as a buffer is very important, get used to waiting while mobs charge or walking backwards so you can change targets to mez while incoming... timing it so a mob gets mezzed in range of the group while they fight another makes things so much easier.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
