				<td colspan="2"><span>I had an odd event occur to me the other day.
<br />

<br />
I try to mez a caster on the pull.  It resists.  I wait with LoS on the caster.  It tries to nuke me.  It tries to nuke me again.  I am watching it the entire time.  I move off to force a break in LoS in order to &quot;pull&quot; it.  3 mobs come.
<br />

<br />
The only thing I can think of that would explain this would be that from where the mob was casting, no other mobs were in aggro range of it.  The minute I broke LoS, and it moved towards me, it ran into aggro range of 2 other mobs and pulled them.
<br />

<br />
It suprised the h*ll out of me, since I didn't think there was enough room between the casting mob and the &quot;arch&quot; such that any mobs between the casting mob and the &quot;arch&quot; wouldn't of been aggro immediately....</span></td>
